Mackinaw Trail Middle School
August 23 at 11:53 AM ·

Meet Mrs. Damgard - 6 & 7th grade counselor.

Mrs. Damgard is an amazing part of
our staff. She’s there for students to share in their joy, help with friendships, worries, sadness, academic success or any other feelings that arise.

She handles all class scheduling and is really great at connecting families with community resources - food assistance, clothing, local counseling services, and so much more!

School counselors are there to help meet the needs of students and families, and Mrs. Damgard is here for YOU! 💙

Alicia.damgard@cadillacschools.org

post_text: Welcome home Charlie Rockwell - Director of the Cadillac Viking Bands. #CadillacExcellencd #VikingPride #CAPSReady #CadillacAlum
shared_text:
Carlie Kaye Rockwell
August 20 at 10:22 PM ·

Tomorrow marks the end of Charlie’s first band camp with the Cadillac Viking Band...as director, rather than student! It’s been so exciting and fun to watch him in this role. He’s received such a warm welcome from the community that raised and taught him. The support he’s received from the band boosters alone is so tremendous...I just don’t have adequate words for their awesomeness! Sewing face coverings for students to wear while playing and covering bells per MSBOA recommendations couldn’t slow this group of boosters!

It is such a glorious sight to watch people come together to keep our community safe, our children involved, and the arts alive. Feeling very fortunate to be here. 💙💛

This doesn’t replace an official graduation, still tentatively scheduled for June 28th @ 2:00.

Extra! Extra! Read All About It!

We are very proud to see our 6th grade student work published in the Cadillac News! As part of our distance learning, students worked on a cross curricular project in which they wrote essays and completed artwork all from home.

Teachers worked with students throughout the week via instructional videos, e-mail, and Google Classroom to complete the work in preparation for publishing. Look for more short essays each day through Flag Day (June 14)!

May 5: Today's featured senior student-athletes are Tipp Baker and Jill Cool. Tipp was a team captain on this year's district championship football team and BNC championship basketball team. Tipp's favorite memories were sharing those championship experiences with his teammates, family and friends. Tipp will attend CMU in the fall to work towards becoming a plastic surgeon. Jill was a leader on the girls ski team and was a main contributor all season long. Jill's favorite memory was ski regionals her junior year where her and her teammates battled the elements and qualified for the state finals. Jill will be attending MSU in the fall. Go Vikes!!

Up North Arts, Inc.
April 26 at 12:17 AM ·

Up North Arts is proud to offer the community a fun and exciting art activity for families with children grades K-12. Art with a Heart is a community art project made possible by a generous donation from Avon Protection Systems. Up North Arts is dedicated to fostering the love and practice of art in our community, especially young people. We have designed a Yard Sign project to keep young people creating art, even though school is not in session. Make something beautiful and share it with the world. Stop by the Up North Arts Center at 601 Chestnut Street to pick up your sign. See detailed instructions below. This runs from April 27th through May 13th. We will be showcasing photos of the signs on Facebook. Have fun! We can't wait to see your artwork.

post_text:
Hi Seniors: This is the latest update for SENIORS only. We all understand the stress of not knowing what may happen to your remaining days at CHS. However, please note we are working hard to get all the answers. We are working with CTC on awarding credit if needed. We also have been reviewing each person’s transcript and comparing them to state graduation requirements. We have communicated with seniors who need a class or two to finish up the state requirements for graduation. If we did not contact you on Friday with courses that must be completed in order to graduate, we encourage you to stay connected by working on suggested work made by your teachers.

We are not planning on canceling activities like prom or graduation, but we are seeking alternative dates to reschedule if needed.

At this point, please continue to stay active and engaged. We will update you as soon as we have more information on our remaining days. Stay healthy and be well!
text:
Hi Seniors: This is the latest update for SENIORS only. We all understand the stress of not knowing what may happen to your remaining days at CHS. However, please note we are working hard to get all the answers. We are working with CTC on awarding credit if needed. We also have been reviewing each person’s transcript and comparing them to state graduation requirements. We have communicated with seniors who need a class or two to finish up the state requirements for graduation. If we did not contact you on Friday with courses that must be completed in order to graduate, we encourage you to stay connected by working on suggested work made by your teachers.

We are not planning on canceling activities like prom or graduation, but we are seeking alternative dates to reschedule if needed.

At this point, please continue to stay active and engaged. We will update you as soon as we have more information on our remaining days. Stay healthy and be well!

“Hi Franklin students! Your challenge for today is to create a challenge for your teacher to complete. This challenge can be academic, physical, or fun. Once you have decided on a challenge, reply to this post with your challenge and your teacher's name. Teachers will pick their favorite challenge, complete, and post for students to see. Be creative and have fun!”

shared_text:
Mackinaw Trail Middle School
March 18 at 11:41 PM ·

Mrs. Schaefer and Mrs. Powell want to thank all the 6th graders that showed up for our live class meeting today (video chat)! We saw 21 smiling 6th graders and got the latest updates on how they’re keeping busy. Almost everyone brought their pet to class, so that was a fun surprise and made for a lot of laughs! We will try to remember the names of all the pets 🐶 for the next class.

*UPDATE*: 5th Graders from Mrs. Freeland/Ms.Williams/Mrs. Koenig's Team also met up for a live class meeting with about the same number of students present as 6th grade! WOW! Students were asking questions about assignments, asking for MORE to do, and enjoyed each other's company. They recorded their class meeting and it is posted on Google Classroom for their team in case anyone was not able to make it.

Everyone had a great time with friends today, and it made us miss you all so much more!! There was a high demand to do this again, so we will schedule another one!! Stay tuned! #MTMSrocks #Vikings 💙💛

Serving daily M-F, 10am-12noon, Drive up only - Cadillac High School/Jr. High Bus Loop. 18 and under FREE, if you are over 18 Breakfast $2, Lunch $3.
NOTE: Friday food service will include weekend meals.
